===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|hamer}}, from {{inh|en|ang|hamor}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*hamar}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*hamaraz||tool with a stone head}} (compare {{cog|fy|hammer}}, {{cog|nds|Hamer}}, {{cog|nl|hamer}}, {{cog|de|Hammer}}, {{cog|da|hammer}}, {{cog|sv|hammare}}). This is traditionally ascribed to {{inh|en|ine-pro|*h₂eḱmoros}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*h₂éḱmō||stone}}, but see {{m|gem-pro|*hamaraz}} for further discussion.

{{sense|declare a defaulter on the stock exchange}} Originally signalled by knocking with a wooden mallet.

